<|startoftext|>Dish: jim s chocolate chip cookies
Directions: preheat oven to 325f
grease a large baking sheet
in a medium pot combine the flour with the baking soda
place over medium-high heat , mix until very bubbly and a little darker in color
whisk for a few minutes to eliminate any flour clumps
increase the heat to medium-high and add vanilla , egg yolk , oil , coffee chips and cinnamon
slowly pour the flour mixture into the pot , and stir constantly until you have a smooth dough
take care not to let any flour overbeep as this can lead to a crusty cookie
add the sugar , salt and baking powder
stir until well combined
divide dough into 16 pieces
roll out to about 1 / 4-inch thickness on lightly floured surface
cut the dough into 1-2-inch squares , about 1 / 4 inch thick
cut into triangles and place , 1 / 2-inch apart , on baking sheet
bake for 10-12 minutes or until edges are browned
bake for a few more minutes to brown bottoms and bottoms
cool on wire rack
remove from baking sheet in a round or square shape
for the topping , combine all ingredients except butter in a small saucepan over low heat
bring just to boiling and simmer 3-4 minutes
immediately remove from heat and stir in butter , 1 / 4 cup at a time , until mixture is to desired consistancy
spread on warm cookies or cookies placed on wax paper
to make the icing , combine the butter , milk and water in a saucepan over low heat
add just enough water to make a soft but not sticky consistency
if necessary , add more water or milk to make desired consistency
stir with a rubber spatula until the mixture is smooth and begins to thicken
remove from heat , if needed , to spread a smooth paste on the sides of the cookie
set cookie aside to set
place cooled cookies on a serving dish , spreading icing evenly over top of cooled cookies
let cookies cool completely before using
these are great to take to parties as gifts
variation:
add 1 / 2 teaspoon powdered sugar or cinnamon to the mixture in the saucepan
i prefer this recipe in the crock pot
use a 3rd
